<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="1341" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,1172,615,711]" box="[212,333,615,639]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1341">
<heading box="[212,333,615,639]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="1341" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,333,615,639]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1341">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[212,1172,615,711]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1341">
The specific name of the new species is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[953,1004,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1341">curti</emphasis>
(= short) plus 
<emphasis box="[212,276,687,711]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1341">fascia</emphasis>
(= band), referring to three short band-like markings on the forewing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
